race.comment: CRIMSON WINGS (10) improving filly with the upside to win this third-up. Strong through the line with the 57.5kg when a tidy second over 1200m at Gosford. Gets map favours and should prove too strong for these. TULIPWOOD (14) come here with a fitness edge over the bulk of these fifth-up. Just over three weeks between runs when she failed to pick them up finishing fourth over 1300m at Canberra. Has further upside and will race closer from the low gate. Each-way contender. MYALABY (11) is undefeated in two starts on her home track and she gets a better setup for this. No match for the smart Duvana when seventh over 1250m at Beaumont (Newcastle). Sure to be thereabouts. HALO PHENOMENA (7) bounced off his good first-up third with a decisive victory in fast time over 1300m at Bathurst. On the up and not to be underrated.
